            <p>Posted by Lam on 12 Aug, 2017</p>
            <p>I have to start off this blog strong by recognizing the most played/competitive game out there at this time. League of legends is a MOBA where you are in teams of 5.
            Your main objective is to work together as a team to destroy the other teams base. There is a huge champion pool to select from with a wide variety of purchasable skins
            for each champion. League of Legends is free for download, the only money you would have to spend is on the optional cosmetic items for champions.</p>
            <p>Although League of Legends is one of the most popular multiplayer online games out right now, it is very known for its toxic communities. There are options to simply
            ignore teammates, but this being a team game that makes it hard to communicate with toxic players to work together. If you can deal with the frustration that a toxic community brings, League of Legends is a very rewarding game that takes high skill to rank up.</p>
