              <div class="col-md-6 abt-left">
                <img src="/index/images/wc3.jpg" alt="" />
                <h3><a href="single.html">Warcraft 3 gets its own PTR!</a></h3>
                <p>Warcraft 3: Reign of Chaos was released in 2002, which for those of you who don't have a calendar handy was roughly 15 years ago. Yet it was just this week that Blizzard announced that it is finally getting its very own public test realm, which Classic Games senior producer Pete Stilwell said will initially be used to test "new Map Pools for 1's, 2's, 3's, 4's and Free-for-All. Read more <a href="http://www.pcgamer.com/warcraft-3-finally-gets-its-own-ptr/">here</a></p>
                <label>August 12, 2017</label>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-6 abt-left">
                <img src="/index/images/sc2.jpg" alt="" />
                <h3><a href="single.html">Google begins training DeepMind AI to dominate players in Starcraft II</a></h3>
                <p>Time and again we have seen machines triumph over humans in various competitions, such as when IBM's Watson beat the best Jeopardy players of all time. More recently, Google's DeepMind AI defeated the world's best Go player. Now AI researchers are setting their sights on StarCraft II, one of the most popular multiplayer games of all time, Wired reports.Read more <a href="http://www.pcgamer.com/google-begins-training-deepmind-ai-to-dominate-players-in-starcraft-ii/">here</a></p>
                <label>August 12, 2017</label>
              </div>
              <div class="clearfix"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="a-1">
              <div class="col-md-6 abt-left">
                <img src="/index/images/fo4.png" alt="" />
                <h3><a href="single.html">Fallout 4 Game of the Year Edition announced, release date set</a></h3>
                <p>Similar to its Washington and New Vegas-set forerunners, Fallout 4 is getting an all-encompassing Game of the Year Edition. Read more <a href="http://www.pcgamer.com/fallout-4-game-of-the-year-edition-announced-release-date-set/">here</a></p>
                <label>August 12, 2017</label>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-6 abt-left">
                <img src="/index/images/pubg.jpg" alt="" />
                <h3><a href="single.html">PUBG brings first-person servers to all game modes, leaderboards incoming</a></h3>
                <p>First-person servers change everything in PlayerUnknown’s Battlegrounds, so reckons Ian Birnbaum, however until now doing so meant playing exclusively in the game's Solo or Duo queues. Now, first-person servers are available in all game modes. Read more <a href="http://www.pcgamer.com/pubg-brings-first-person-servers-to-all-game-modes-leaderboards-incoming/">here</a></p>
                <label>August 12, 2017</label>
